            Concerning the words (beloued) poyze them but judiciouſly, and you ſhall apprehend a whole court of Aſſiſe in the Church, before you come to the Bench. Firſt then let the order of words and conſtruction, giue place vnto the order of Legall proceſse in trials: and then plainely ſee Actorem the plaintife in the perſon of the Widow; and vnder it comprehend the neceſsary ſupporters, Teſtes or witneſses, 
