                  , the burthen of oppreſſion, from the ſhoulders of the innocent. If thoſe 
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                   in the commonwealth of Athens, the Great ones, intruded vpon the aunciently moſt wretched 
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  , the poore Plebeians right, the Tribunall of Solon was immediatly their Sanctuary: and the glory of his wiſdome, was the wiſdome of his government: 
